1️⃣ What is Serialization? (in plain words)

Serialization = converting an object into bytes

Why?

To save object to a file
To send object over network
To store object in DB / cache

🧠 Think:

Object → Bytes

2️⃣ What is Deserialization?

Deserialization = converting bytes back into object

🧠 Think:

Bytes → Object

3️⃣ Real-Life Analogy 📦

Serialization = packing a gift in a box
Deserialization = opening the box and getting the gift back

4️⃣ Simple Java Example

Step 1: Make class Serializable

import java.io.Serializable;

class Employee implements Serializable {
    int id;
    String name;

    Employee(int id, String name) {
        this.id = id;
        this.name = name;
    }
}

📌 implements Serializable is a marker interface (no methods).

Step 2: Serialization (Object → File)

import java.io.*;

public class SerializeDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {

        Employee emp = new Employee(1, "Tanisha");

        ObjectOutputStream oos =
                new ObjectOutputStream(new FileOutputStream("emp.ser"));

        oos.writeObject(emp);
        oos.close();

        System.out.println("Object serialized");
    }
}

Step 3: Deserialization (File → Object)

import java.io.*;

public class DeserializeDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {

        ObjectInputStream ois =
                new ObjectInputStream(new FileInputStream("emp.ser"));

        Employee emp = (Employee) ois.readObject();
        ois.close();

        System.out.println(emp.id + " " + emp.name);
    }
}

5️⃣ Key Rules (Very Important)

🔹 Serializable Interface

implements Serializable

Marker interface
-Tells JVM: “This object CAN be serialized”

🔹 transient keyword

transient String password;

Field will NOT be serialized

Used for sensitive data

🔹 serialVersionUID

private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;

-Version control for serialized objects
-Prevents InvalidClassException

6️⃣ Why Serialization is Used?

-HTTP session storage
-Caching (Redis, Hazelcast)
-RMI
-Deep copy of objects

7️⃣ Interview One-Liners ⭐

Q: What is serialization?

“Serialization is the process of converting an object into a byte stream so it can be stored or transmitted.”

Q: What is deserialization?

“Deserialization is the reverse process of converting a byte stream back into an object.”

8️⃣ Common Pitfalls ❌

-Static fields ❌ (not serialized)
-Transient fields ❌
-Non-serializable child objects ❌
-Changing class after serialization ❌

9️⃣ Bonus: Relation to Singleton (Trick Question)

👉 Normal singleton can break during deserialization
👉 Enum singleton does NOT break

🔥 Interview gold.